Las antenas de telefonía y sus trabajadores
Es una historia impactante (y un poco larga) sobre los trabajadores que montan antenas de telefonía en EEUU: <a href="http://www.propublica.org/article/cell-tower-fatalities">In Race For Better Cell Service, Men Who Climb Towers Pay With Their Lives</a>.

<blockquote>
"It's the wild, wild west of the technology industry," said Victor Guerrero, a construction project manager and former climber. "You've got to have a problem to hang 150 feet in the air on an 8-inch strap. You've got to be insane."
</blockquote>

